import pandas as pd

df = pd.DataFrame({'name': ['jon','sam','jane','bob'],
           'age': [30,25,18,26],
           'sex':['male','male','female','male']})

row = ['45', 'Dean', 'male']
# Add the row at top in df
df.loc[-1] = row
df.index = df.index + 1
# Sort the DataFrame by index in ascending order and modify the original DataFrame
df.sort_index(inplace=True)
